# Deployment (EAS / TestFlight)

## Prerequisites

- User needs: Expo account, Apple Developer ($99/yr) for App Store/TestFlight.
- Never commit Apple credentials or API keys.

## Configuration

- Bundle identifier must be unique (e.g. `com.username.appname`) in `app.json` or `app.config.js`.
- Run `eas build:configure` before first cloud build.

## Commands (user runs in terminal)

```bash
npm install -g eas-cli
eas login
eas build:configure
eas build --platform ios
eas submit --platform ios
```

## Secrets

- Use EAS Secrets or `.env` for API keys — never hardcode in app source.

## Expo Go vs production

- Expo Go is dev only. TestFlight builds are standalone — verify without `expo start` running.

## When build fails

- Read full EAS log; common fixes: bundle ID conflict, missing icon, invalid app.json fields.
